    {
      "id": "context-compat-contract",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Context Compatibility Contract",
      "position": {
        "x": -40,
        "y": 120
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Context Compatibility Contract\n\nCompatibility is not just about autorun code. It includes:\n- structure\n- authority\n- execution\n- entry surfaces\n\nA graph is expansion-safe only if those dimensions can be projected into host context without breaking host rules.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
